text: Okanogan ( ) is a city in Okanogan County, Washington, United States. The population was 2,379 at the 2020 census, within the Greater Omak Area. It is the seat of Okanogan County. Official incorporation of Okanogan took place on October 29, 1907. ==References== Category:Cities in Washington (state) Category:County seats in Washington (state)
